ZCODE ITALIC START--><i> for that particular mob</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->.<br><br>If that's right, each mob we fight has some magic AC. When we hit that AC, we should stop optimizing AC and go for HP, or wis, or whatever is next-best in your situation. We should be able to run tests and find the optimum AC for fungus shrooms, for orc pawns, for HoT mobs, for Dozekar.<br><br>Does this sound reasonable?<br><br>Dunster<br>60 Crusadah<br>Cruel Efficiency<br>Brell Serilis <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uvarutiasilvon.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Varutia Silvon</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Noble Squire</span><br>  Posts: 49<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(4/24/02 10:59:52 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathfrm13.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=179.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: AC Effectivenes, aka &quot;The AC Soft-Cap&quot;</span><hr size=1> Which could mean most of mob in old world, you can live with 900ac, kunark with 1100 etc. This just means it varies mob to mob, but having that level of ac, you'd do okie with most of mob in those areas, which in rough term translates into something people need to work towards in order to tank effectivly. Adjusting equipments per situation has always been the case.<br><br><br> <p><center><a href=http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=177561>Varutia Silvonesit </a><BR>Level 55 Knight<BR>Terris Thule</center><BR></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/usenchy.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Senchy</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Blessed Protector</span><br>  Posts: 425<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(4/25/02 4:36:36 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathfrm13.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=179.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: AC Effectivenes, aka &quot;The AC Soft-Cap&quot;</span><hr size=1> What you wrote is my believe =)<br><br>Adjust AC to the attack rating of a mob. <p>Senchy Solariatus <BR>60 Crusader of Rodcet Nife<BR>56 Chanter of Rodcet Nife (Tymbor)<BR>Dol Amroth<BR><a href=http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=79641>Typical Raid Setup</a><BR><a href=http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=66884>AC Solo Gear</a><BR></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ukindreth.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Kindreth</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Wandering Knight</span><br>  Posts: 137<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(4/25/02 7:38:38 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathfrm13.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=179.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://home.earthlink.net/~acastillo1/Images/EQ/knight.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: AC Effectivenes, aka &quot;The AC Soft-Cap&quot;</span><hr size=1> My belief is 1200ac is good enough, after that concentrate on Hp, resist and wis. <p><p style="line-height: 100%; word-spacing: 0; margin-top: 0; margin-bottom: 0"><b><font color="#C0C0C0"><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=168320"><font size="3" face="Times New Roman">Kinny</font></a><font size="3" face="Times New Roman">&amp; <a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=178342">Kindreth</a>Trinity </font></font></b></p><p style="line-height: 100%; word-spacing: 0; margin-top: 0; margin-bottom: 0"><b><font size="3" face="Times New Roman"><a href="http://www.dkguild.net"><font color="#C0C0C0">DeathKnights</font></a></font></b></p><p style="line-height: 100%; word-spacing: 0; margin-top: 0; margin-bottom: 0"><b><font size="3" face="Times New Roman" color="#C0C0C0">Xegony</font></b></p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ubizomb.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Bizomb</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Fatcat </span><br>  Posts: 1043<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(4/25/02 8:03:20 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathfrm13.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=179.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: AC Effectivenes, aka &quot;The AC Soft-Cap&quot;</span><hr size=1> I always said that you have to base it on the attack rating of the mob. I don't think there is anything hardcoded.<br><br>Even tho I don't believe in the softcap per se. I am still shooting for 1200ish ac and then I'm going to try to max out my hp. Once you get higher than that, it's a matter of finding mobs with attack rating high enough to make your extra ac matter.They start to get fewer and far between so generally you won't need anything higher. <br><br>I'd guess on some NTOV mobs you could raise your ac by 200 points and still gain reasonable benefit from it. But why sacrifice a ton of hp and whatnot for the ability to tank a single mob a bit better?<br><br>Biz. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uaalek.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Aalek</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Wandering Knight</span><br>  Posts: 182<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(4/25/02 8:24:14 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathfrm13.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=179.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: AC Effectivenes, aka &quot;The AC Soft-Cap&quot;</span><hr size=1> I'd also say that mobs with insane attack ratings are most likely going to require /disc defensive, so once your AC is high enough to tank the mobs you can/do tank, your AC is high enough and HPs etc. will benefit you more.  IMO going from 1200 to 1300 or even 1400 AC isn't going to make a huge difference in which mobs you will be able to effectively tank.  <br><br>Let the warriors pile up on the insanely high AC gear while you get the gear that works better for Paladins. <p><BR><a href=http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=131249>Aalek</a><BR>60 Crusader<BR>Reign in Power<BR>Torvonnilous</p><i></i></td></tr></table><table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top"> </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathfrm13.showPrevMessage?topicID=179.topic"> << Prev Topic</a>&nbsp;| <a href="http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathfrm13.showNextMessage?topicID=179.topic"> Next Topic >> </a><br><br><a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathfrm13.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=179.topic&index=5><img src=http://eq1.castersrealm.com/pon/images/reply.gif border=0 alt="Add Reply"></a> </td></tr></table><br><table width=95% border=0><td valign="top"> <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathfrm13.emailToFriend?topicID=179.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/image/email.gif border=0 alt="Email This To a Friend"> Email This To a Friend</a><br> <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathfrm13.threadControl?topicID=179.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/professional/deleteThread.gif border=0 alt="Topic Control Image"> Topic Commands (Moderator only)</a><br> <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathfrm13.subscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=179.topic>Subscribe</a> Click to receive email notification of replies<br>  <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathfrm13.unsubscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=179.topic>Unsubscribe</a> Click to stop receiving email notificatio